Summary of actions and result

1) Initial compilation check (run_github_action #1)
- I ran the build (./gradlew clean compileJava) via the GitHub Actions workflow.
- Result: compilation failed. The compiler reported 32 errors across multiple processors referencing missing methods/fields on the entity classes (examples):
  - User: getLifecycleState(), setLifecycleState(String), setUpdatedAt(String), getTechnicalId()
  - ImportJob: getTechnicalId(), setNotificationSent(boolean), setUpdatedAt(String), getNotificationSent()
- These failures indicate processor code expects additional fields / helper methods on the entity classes (User and ImportJob).

2) Fixes applied
I updated the entity classes used by the processors to provide the fields / helpers the processors expect.

Files changed (paths):
- src/main/java/com/java_template/application/entity/user/version_1/User.java
  - Added fields: private String lifecycleState; private String updatedAt;
  - Added compatibility helpers:
    - public String getTechnicalId() { return this.id; }
    - public void setTechnicalId(String technicalId) { this.id = technicalId; }
  - Note: Lombok's @Data supplies getters/setters for lifecycleState and updatedAt.

- src/main/java/com/java_template/application/entity/importjob/version_1/ImportJob.java
  - Added fields: private Boolean notificationSent; private String updatedAt;
  - Added compatibility helpers:
    - public String getTechnicalId() { return this.jobId; }
    - public void setTechnicalId(String technicalId) { this.jobId = technicalId; }

(These changes provide the methods and fields referenced by processors such as setUpdatedAt, getTechnicalId, getNotificationSent, setNotificationSent, and lifecycleState accessors.)

3) Verification compilation check (run_github_action #2)
- I re-ran the same GitHub Actions workflow to verify the fixes.
- Result: BUILD SUCCESSFUL, compile step completed with no errors.
  - The workflow output included: "✅ Compilation successful - no errors found" and "BUILD SUCCESSFUL".

